text: Seneasha Creek is a stream in the U.S. state of Mississippi. Seneasha is a name derived from the Choctaw language purported to mean either "sycamores are there" or "sycamore river". Variant names are "Seneatcha", "Senesha Creek", and "Sineasha". ==References== Category:Rivers of Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Attala County, Mississippi
title: Seneasha Creek
